student affairs residential education about east campus west campus independent living for staff stanford university student affairs all stanford search submit introduction fraternities and sororities have been a part of stanford since the first day the university opened in 1891 greeks have enjoyed a vibrant and dynamic existence at stanford and today represent 13 of the undergraduate student population currently 28 greek organizations are formally recognized by the university ten are housed on stanford's campus seven fraternities and three sororities residents purchase the house board plan for meals as they each hire a house cook bedrooms vary in size and shape from singles to five person rooms residents for greek houses are chosen through the annual rush process if you are interested in joining a sorority or fraternity please go to greek life at stanford undergraduate residences academic language & culture houses ethnic cross cultural theme houses focus theme houses greek houses cooperative living houses self operated houses freshman sophomore houses frosoco apartments & suites residence halls home student affairs the student affairs division is responsible for programs and services that focus on students and their stanford experience while also engaging with faculty staff parents alumni and the community at large copyright 2011 stanford university terms of use copyright complaints report a problem with this site
